cards.d: A large group of people or things gathered closely together is massing.
cards.s: Protesters are massing in the city square for the demonstration.

cards.d: it means something that is burning with bright flames or is very hot.
cards.s: The campfire was flaming brightly in the dark night.

cards.d: it is something of little value or importance.
cards.s: She spent the afternoon arguing over a mere trifle instead of focusing on what truly mattered.

cards.d: it means speaking in an annoyed or impatient way.
cards.s: She responded testily when asked the same question for the third time.

cards.d: Having unlimited power or authority.
cards.s: The king believed he was almighty and could control everything in his kingdom.

cards.d: it is a wide smile that shows your teeth.
cards.s: She couldn’t help but grin when she saw her surprise birthday party.

cards.d: To gently push someone or something with your elbow or a light touch.
cards.s: She nudged her friend to get her attention before pointing at the bird.

cards.d: Water or another liquid falling slowly in small drops.
cards.s: The faucet was dripping all night and kept me awake.

cards.d: An omen is a sign or event believed to predict something good or bad in the future.
cards.s: Seeing a black cat cross your path is often considered a bad omen.

cards.d: In a way that shows great joy or satisfaction after a victory or success.
cards.s: She raised her arms triumphantly after crossing the finish line first.

cards.d: Taking a longer or more complicated route instead of the most direct one.
cards.s: She gave a circuitous explanation that took twenty minutes to avoid admitting she was wrong.

cards.d: Too great or extreme to be expressed in words.
cards.s: The beauty of the sunset over the ocean left her with an ineffable feeling of peace.

cards.d: People or teams competing to win something.
cards.s: The two teams were strong contenders for the championship title this year.

cards.d: Having many bends and curves like a snake.
cards.s: The road wound in a serpentine path up the mountain.

cards.d: Reducing something to small particles or powder by crushing it.
cards.s: She spent the morning grinding coffee beans for the café.

cards.d: To a very great extent or degree.
cards.s: She enjoyed the concert immensely and couldn’t stop talking about it.

cards.d: Covered with many green plants or parts of plants that grow from stems or branches.
cards.s: The park has a leafy path perfect for a quiet walk.

cards.d: The remaining unsmoked part of a cigarette.
cards.s: He picked up the dogend from the ground and put it in the ashtray.

cards.d: People who are responsible for supervising or managing a particular place or group of people.
cards.s: The park wardens reminded visitors to stay on the marked trails to protect the wildlife.

cards.d: Covered with dirt or messy.
cards.s: The child's hands were grubby after playing in the garden all afternoon.

cards.d: Made an angry or annoyed facial expression by frowning and lowering the eyebrows.
cards.s: The child scowled when his mother told him he couldn’t have any more candy.

cards.d: To have no confidence or faith in someone or something because you believe they may be dishonest or unreliable.
cards.s: She distrusted the stranger who offered her a ride home late at night.

cards.d: Containers used for holding waste until it is collected.
cards.s: Please take out the trash and empty all the dustbins in the house.

cards.d: Showing deep religious commitment and sincere belief.
cards.s: She is a devout follower of her faith and attends services every week.

cards.d: In a way that suggests something bad or unpleasant is likely to happen.
cards.s: The dark clouds gathered ominously over the quiet town.

cards.d: In a way that shows a feeling of longing or sadness for something lost or unattainable.
cards.s: She looked wistfully at the old photograph of her childhood home.

cards.d: A building where a community of nuns live and work.
cards.s: She decided to join the convent after finishing her studies.

cards.d: A set of beliefs or aims that guide someone's actions.
cards.s: Many people live by the creed that honesty is the best policy.
